cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving the accuracy of supervised NLP models using semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for semi-supervised learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using a Bi-LSTM sentence encoder, which is a common technique in computer vision, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possibility. Finally, the paper mentions using auxiliary prediction modules, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
